	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />I got the adapters and got everything wired up, but the chip isn't giving me an ID yet. :\
<br />
<br />I'm going to solder another 29F032 to an adapter board in an effort to isolate the problem. Checking all the leads on the adapter seems to work okay, though it might be the ZIF socket I installed in the adapter not correctly contacting all of the pins. Hard to test.
<br />
<br />rkrenicki: Firstly, thanks again for sharing the PCB design. I have some thoughts about the adapter board design... maybe make the board a tad longer? A ZAF socket and the A19-21 pins at the end are a ridiculously tight fit! The holes were a good size this time for sure though. Might also be nice to have holes for the extra 4 legs on a 40 pin ZIF even if they don't actually need to be soldered. Bending them out of the way is okay I guess, but it'd be tidier just having a few more holes on a slightly longer board. The boards are cheap enough that adding another half inch or so isn't really going to cause any significant boost in their price.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
